    • getPropertyPrefixes

      protected List<String> getPropertyPrefixes()
      Prefixes added to property names. Override to implement namespacing of properties for elements with multiple semantic mappings. Multiple prefixes may be used for profiles. For example, an element may have one mapping for documentation, another for code generation, and one more for status updates - pulling runtime information from monitoring systems and updating diagram elements with health status.
      Returns:
      This implementation returns a singleton list of an empty string;

    • setParent

      protected void setParent(ProcessorConfig<P> config, P processor, ProcessorInfo<P> parentProcessorInfo, ProgressMonitor progressMonitor, Consumer<Throwable> failureConsumer)
      Description copied from class: AbstractEObjectFactory
      Sets parent. If parent is null this method sets itself to be called for the grand parent etc. If child reference property is not null then the semantic element is injected into the parent's references specified in the child reference property. Otherwise, if parent reference property is not null then the parent is injected into the semantic element's reference specified in the parent reference property.
      Overrides:
      setParent in class AbstractEObjectFactory<T extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject,P extends SemanticProcessor<T>>
